<para>
  Apply all of the given &mesh;'s &field; <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Mesh-InitialConditions">initializers</link>
  at the &mesh;'s current <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Mesh-Time">time</link>,
  <emphasis>and</emphasis> set the &mesh;'s <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Mesh-Time">time</link> to the given
  value.  This sets the values of the &fields; at all of the &nodes;
  where the &fields; are <link
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Mesh.Field.Define">defined</link>, if an
  initializer has been <link
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Mesh.Set_Field_Initializer">assigned</link> to
  the &field;.
</para>
<para>
  To set the &field; values without changing the time, use <xref
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Mesh.Apply_Field_Initializers"/> instead.
</para>
<para>
  In the GUI, this command is invoked by the <link
  linkend="Section-Tasks-Solver-ApplyInit"><guibutton>Apply</guibutton></link>
  button in the <link
  linkend="Section-Tasks-Solver-FieldInitPane"><guilabel>Field
  Initialization</guilabel></link> pane of the <link
  linkend="Section-Tasks-Solver">Solver</link> page.
</para>

